}

Class level lock and instance level lock both are different. Both don’t interfere each other lock status. If one instance of a class has already got locked by a thread then another thread can’t get lock for that instance until unless lock is freed by first thread.
Same behaviour is there for class level lock.

But if a thread acquires Class level lock then another thread can acquire lock on one of its instance. Both can work parallel.`

